entry.title: Reland "SimpleCache: fix crash w/iterator entry doom concurrent w/bulk doom"
entry.content:
This is a reland of commit d6b97570330071cd3070af3d0cbce20ac1866bce



(Proper fix of regression caused by it upcoming as a separate CL)



Original change's description:

> SimpleCache: fix crash w/iterator entry doom concurrent w/bulk doom

>

> The trouble was that entries opened via hash were not kept track of in active_entries_ until the open succeeded, and so the usual rules of letting an entry object take care of its own doom if it is around was not followed if a mass doom happened in that window.

>

> So change the code to add the fresh entry to active_entries_ during open-by-hash just as it would be during a regular open. This does mean that active_entries_ sometimes has entries that don't have their key set yet, so the key in SimpleEntryImpl and SimpleSynchronousEntry was changed to be explicitly an optional, to make sure we never get confused --- it should be set by the time it's every user-visible, but now there will be angry absl::optional CHECKs if we screw up. (This also can avoid some confusion between empty key and key not set).

entry.title: Change the recording condition of AUTOCOMPLETE_SUGGESTION_SHOWN metric
entry.content:
Per histogram guidelines [1], a new metric was created here:

crrev.com/c/5050050 .



This metric was recorded every time the shown suggestion were not of the

"autofill" type.

The issue was that there are also many types of suggestions which are

not of "autofill" type, neither "autocomplete" type.

Thus, the metric was recorded in situations it was not supposed to be.



This CL changes the signature of DidShowSuggestions:

Instead of "bool has_autofill_suggestions", now there is a vector of

`PopupItemId`.

Now, if one wants to see whether the suggestion have the type

"autofill", "autocomplete" or anything else, it is possible within the

`DidShowSuggestions` method.



[1] https://chromium.googlesource.com/chromium/src/tools/+/HEAD/metrics/histograms/README.md#Revising-Histograms

entry.title: Make lifetimes more natural in AutofillExternalDelegate test.
entry.content:
This CL performs a few clean-ups in the AED test:

- Instead of having separate fixture members for the driver, the

manager and the external delegate, there is now only a driver which

owns the manager which owns the external delegate. This reflects

ownership and lifetimes in production.

- There are now getters for the client, the driver, the manager,

and the external delegate.

- The tear-down method is no longer needed.

- There is now an additional fixture method to destroy the driver and

its children prior to tear down which is needed in one test.



All the other changes in the CL are just renamings from member

variable to getter.

entry.title: Fix MockNetworkTransaction's callback call order
entry.content:
Currently MockNetworkTransaction is calling callbacks in a wrong order.

The current order is:

1. modify_request_headers_callback_

2. before_network_start_callback_

3. connected_callback_

But this should be:

1. before_network_start_callback_

2. connected_callback_

2. modify_request_headers_callback_



Also there is a bug that if `before_network_start_callback_` sets

`defer`, `connected_callback_` is never called.



This CL fixes the bug and the order of callbacks by using the

DoLoop pattern.

https://chromium.googlesource.com/chromium/src/+/master/net/docs/code-patterns.md#doloop



Also this CL adds some tests for MockNetworkTransaction.
